@startuml AdriaBOX_Fault_Tolerance_Sequence
!theme plain
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title AdriaBOX - Fault Tolerance & Dynamic Replication (Zoom Level 1)

participant "Metadata Server" as server
database "SQLite DB" as db
participant "Storage Node A\n(Crashes)" as nodeA
participant "Storage Node B\n(Replica Holder)" as nodeB
participant "Storage Node C\n(New Target)" as nodeC

== Normal Operation (Heartbeats) ==

nodeA -> server : 1. Heartbeat (I am alive)
nodeB -> server : 2. Heartbeat (I am alive)
nodeC -> server : 3. Heartbeat (I am alive)

== Failure Detection ==

note over nodeA : Node A suddenly crashes\nor loses network connection
x- nodeA -> server : 4. (Heartbeat Missing)

server -> server : 5. Timeout Triggered (e.g., 10 seconds)

server -> db : 6. Update state: Mark Node A as OFFLINE\nQuery: Find under-replicated chunks
activate db
db --> server : 7. Result: Chunk1 needs replication\n(Surviving replica is on Node B)
deactivate db

== Dynamic Replication (Auto-Healing) ==

server -> nodeB : 8. Command: Replicate Chunk1 to Node C
activate nodeB

nodeB -> nodeC : 9. TCP Connect & Send Chunk1 (Binary)
activate nodeC
nodeC -> nodeC : 10. Write to Docker Volume
nodeC --> nodeB : 11. TCP ACK (Saved)
deactivate nodeC

nodeB --> server : 12. 200 OK (Replication Successful)
deactivate nodeB

server -> db : 13. Update Index (Chunk1 is now on B and C)

@enduml

